.TH lr "" "" Command
.PC "List subdirectories' contents in columnar format"
\fBlr [\fIfile ...\^\fB]\fR
.PP
.B lr
is a link to the command
.BR "ls \-CR" .
It prints each
.I file
in columnar format, like the command
.BR lc .
If a
.I file
is a directory,
.B lr
also prints its contents and that of each of its subdirectories.
If no
.I file
is named, it lists the contents of the current directory by default.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "commands," commands
.Xr "l," l
.Xr "lc," lc
.Xr "lf," lf
.Xr "ls," ls
.Xr "lx" lx
